###  http://futaoo.github.io/ncv/Attribute
:Attribute rdf:type owl:Class ;
           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "All attributes must be measurable, so that targets can be set as part of the conservation objective for the feature."@en ,
                                                  "Attributes should describe the condition of the feature and not the factors which influence it. For example, management activities are not suitable attributes."@en .


###  http://futaoo.github.io/ncv/Condition
:Condition rdf:type owl:Class ;
           <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Condition of interest features can be presented such as: \"Favourable - maintained\", \"Favourable - recovered\", \"Unfavourable - recovering\", \"Unfavourable - no change\", \"Unfavourable - declining\", \"Partially destroyed\", \"Destroyed\" ."@en .


###  http://futaoo.github.io/ncv/ConservationObjective
:ConservationObjective rdf:type owl:Class ;
                       rdfs:subClassOf [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                         owl:onProperty :hasFeatureOfInterest ;
                                         owl:qualifiedCardinality "1"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger ;
                                         owl:onClass :FeatureOfInterest
                                       ] ;
                       <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Conservation objectives will be prepared for each interest feature on each site. These objectives contain targets or target ranges which should be met if the feature is to be judged to be in favourable condition."@en .


###  http://futaoo.github.io/ncv/DesignatedSite
:DesignatedSite rdf:type owl:Class ;
                <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "A designated site refers to a specific geographic area that has been officially identified and set aside for protection or conservation due to its environmental, ecological, cultural, or historical significance. These sites are typically protected by national or international laws and regulations to ensure the preservation of important natural habitats, species, or cultural features."@en .


###  http://futaoo.github.io/ncv/FeatureOfInterest
:FeatureOfInterest rdf:type owl:Class ;
                   <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The features to be monitored are known as the interest features for which the site has been notified or designated."@en .


###  http://futaoo.github.io/ncv/Habitat
:Habitat rdf:type owl:Class ;
         rdfs:subClassOf :FeatureOfInterest .


###  http://futaoo.github.io/ncv/Species
:Species rdf:type owl:Class ;
         rdfs:subClassOf :FeatureOfInterest .


###  http://futaoo.github.io/ncv/Target
:Target rdf:type owl:Class ;
        <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Targets should be set to ensure that habitats and species populations are maintained in a condition which is likely to be sustained over the foreseeable feature, in line with the principles of favourable conservation status."@en .


###  http://futaoo.github.io/ncv/TargetDriver
:TargetDriver rdf:type owl:Class ;
              <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "General class for drivers influencing conservation targets. Such drivers can be  \"maintain\", \"reduce\", \"recover\", \"increase\", or \"no decline\" which are varying according to the standards in different countries."@en .


